tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE test_results ( 
   test_id INT PRIMARY KEY, 
   test_name VARCHAR(255), 
   test_result VARCHAR(50), 
   tester_name VARCHAR(100), 
   test_date DATE 
 );

CREATE TABLE test_results (result_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
                     test_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
                     test_date DATE NOT NULL,
                     test_result VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL);

CREATE TABLE test_observations (observation_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
                        result_id INT NOT NULL,
                        observation_notes TEXT,
                        observation_date DATE NOT NULL);

CREATE TABLE test_personnel (person_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
                      person_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
                      person_role VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
                      department VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL);

CREATE TABLE test_logs (
    log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    test_id INT,
    tester_id INT,
    result_description TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (test_id) REFERENCES test_results(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (tester_id) REFERENCES testers(tester_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Testers (
    tester_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    tester_name STRING,
    tester_email STRING
)

CREATE TABLE Tests (
    test_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    test_name STRING,
    test_description STRING
)

CREATE TABLE TestResults (
    result_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    tester_id UUID,
    test_id UUID,
    result_status STRING
)

CREATE TABLE TestLogs (
    log_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    tester_id UUID,
    test_id UUID,
    log_message STRING
)

CREATE TABLE TestScores (
    score_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    tester_id UUID,
    test_id UUID,
    test_score INT
)
